What are the implications of widespread Linux use in the Third World? 

- Women and girls who were previously denied educational opportunities will be
  able to establish themselves as insular, boring, pedantic geeks on an equal 
  footing with men.

- The long-standing argument about vi versus emacs will be settled with a 
  truckload of black market AK-47s.

- In some cultures, bloated software will actually be considered more attractive

- Indian CS undergrads will be able to talk about how great the internet was 
  in the good old days, before all the clueless n00bs arrived.

- Third World businesses will have access to new markets for their agricultural 
  produce, manufacturing services, and r3d H0+ z3r0-d4y w4R32.

- The highways on the internet will not become more few.
