A blue-chip client is being shown around a consulting company's offices by the 
VC. As they walk the floor they pass a barefoot and bearded man in a t-shirt 
and jeans.

The client looks unimpressed and asks the VC what the barefooted man's role is 
within the company. The VC replies, "I don't know, but he must be very good at 
it."
