%
I've seen similar things before, like a programmer with years of experience 
not knowing that there's anything faster than Bubble Sort. 

I think this is a good counterexample to the people who say that CS degrees 
are pointless since most of the content is never used. Self-taught programmers 
can often have big gaps in their knowledge like this, since they've never had 
to learn boring stuff like data structures. And since it's an unknown unknown, 
they're not aware that they're missing anything.
